        The dietary assessment forms were extensive.

        Holloway announced via fruiting bodies arranged around the medical chamber.
        "Section One: Basic Nutritional Requirements."
        "Daily caloric intake range?"

        Kira's stomach growled loud enough that Scout bounced anxiously.
        Kira rubbed her face — "Approximately two thousand calories per day for baseline maintenance."

        "Excellent! Macronutrient ratios?" Holloway asked.

        Kira rubbed her face again — "I don't… Balanced — carbohydrates, proteins, fats, the usual human stuff."

        "Could you be more specific?"

        Her stomach was eating itself from the inside.

        Kira — "Forty percent carbs, thirty percent protein, thirty percent fat — roughly. I'm a cargo specialist, not a nutritionist."

        "Noted! Buddy, can you provide more detailed nutritional data from Kira's medical file?"

        Buddy said, "Accessing records now — Kira's optimal nutritional profile includes complete proteins with essential amino acids, complex carbohydrates, essential fatty acids, and a comprehensive vitamin and mineral panel. Shall I list each micronutrient requirement?"

        "Please do!"

        This was going to take forever.

        Mushrooms were fruiting throughout the chamber—Remedy's network responding to the discussion. The robot stood to one side, observing.

        Remedy said, "While we document requirements, I'm analyzing which compounds I can synthesize from available plant chemistry. Proteins are possible — I can fruit mushrooms with complete amino acid profiles. Carbohydrates, easy. Some fats. Vitamins will be… challenging."

        "How challenging?" Kira asked.

        Remedy — "Vitamin B12 might be impossible. Some others I can approximate through fungal compounds, but they won't be identical to what you're used to."

        Great. Alien vitamin deficiency to look forward to.

        Holloway announced — "Section Two: Dietary Restrictions. Do you follow any religious or cultural dietary guidelines?"

        Kira stared at the fruiting body — "Are you serious?"

        "Dietary preferences are very important for individual wellness!" Holloway replied.

        Kira — "I crashed on an alien planet, my ship is wreckage — I'll eat whatever won't kill me."

        "I understand you're in unusual circumstances, but we want to respect cultural practices! For example: kosher requirements? Halal guidelines? Vegetarian preferences?" Holloway pressed.

        Her stomach made a sound like dying machinery.

        Kira — "No religious restrictions — no cultural requirements — no vegetarian preferences — *I will eat *literally anything edible*."

        "Wonderful! Very flexible dietary parameters. Next: favorite cuisines or flavor profiles?" Holloway asked.

        Scout bumped against her leg sympathetically.

        Kira — "You're asking my favorite cuisines while I haven't eaten in thirty-six hours."

        "Context helps us provide optimal nutrition!"

        Kira — "My favorite cuisine is _food_ — any food, all food."

        Buddy added, "Kira's consumption history suggests preference for protein-rich meals, minimal processed sugars, occasional chocolate as treat food. Spice tolerance: moderate."
      </text>
